  "description": "Generally accepted accounting principles (GAAP) are the set of accounting standards, conventions, and rules that govern financial reporting in the United States. The Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB) sets and maintains GAAP, updating it through Accounting Standards Updates (ASUs).",
